                    <li>p</li>
                    <li>h1, h2, h3</li>
                    <li>ul/ol, li</li>
                    <li>strong</li>
                    <li>em</li>
                    <li>img</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>Your page must include photos. Who wants to see a recipe without photos!</p>
                  <p>Your Recipe should also contain 2 sections, an ingredients list as well as cooking instructions.</p>

                  <h3>Styling:</h3>
                  <ul class="ul_intro">
                    <li>Use CSS/SASS to add rounded corners to an element on your page.</li>
                    <li>Use a drop shadow on at least one element on your page.</li>
                    <li>Use CSS/SASS to resize and crop the images on your page.</li>
                    <li>Use CSS/SASS to apply hover state style change.</li>
                    <li>Use CSS/SASS to have your hover change use a transition or transformation effect, rather that just suddenly changing.</li>
                  </ul>
                  <br></br>
                  <h3>Tips:</h3>
                  <ul class="ul_intro">
                    <li>Make sure you are using a code editor, we recommend using Sublime Text.</li>
                    <li>Use Google Chrome as your default browser, this make using Dev Tools more natural.</li>
                    <li>Use Chrome Dev-Tools to make minor style changes in your browser for more efficient styling.</li>
                    <li>Keep this assignment well organised. Ensure you keep your project safely stored. Not only will you be submitting this assignment for review later but you will also be making some revisions to the code using JavaScript and J-Quer later on in the course.</li>
                  </ul>
